<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>if Guild xyz has been trying to get onto the Sev Rot, and they have umpteen folks on early on a Saturday morning, and they see Sev up, I really don't think that they are going to have someone log off, come check the RTA board to see if another guild has newly entered the Rot just the spawn before, and say &quot;oh, gee, shucks, we can't do him today, we'll have to wait another week or seven and hope we can do this again&quot;. Nope, they will just go ahead and kill.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->If that is the way the server etiquette is written, and this guild wants to follow that etiquette, there should be no reason why they wouldn't check to see if another guild has entered the rotation this turn and leave the mob alone.  Why would they do this?  Because that is the rules that everyone lives by.<br>
<br>
Dembire and I are saying the exact same thing...<br>
<br>
I think the RTA underestimates the respect given to it by the guilds of The Rathe.  We can sit here until pigs fly south for the winter coming up with individual 'what if' scenarios ...the bottom line is, most of those scenarios can exist today, and they don't.  People know the rules and they follow the rules, provided the rules are fair and equitable to everyone concerned.  Certainly you don't want to 'restrict content', but you have to be able to adapt when a rotation is getting freakishly huge like the Sev rotation.  The RTA adapted for the cleric epic, everyone followed that adaptation ...I see this as no different.<br>
<br>
Implementing a &quot;one new guild added to rotation per turn&quot; rule, leaving the second spawn of a turn to the rotation guild for a full 24 hours, seems to me to be a very fair compromise to all concerned.  One new guild gets added per turn (provided they can race the rotation guild to the spawn) and the rotation guild gets their 24 hour shot at the mob.  The rotation keeps rotating ...no one is being discriminated against because their guild only plays between 5:07pm - 5:38pm each night... <br>
