Far Seekers</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dembiredeadbones>Dembire Deadbones</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.w3.org/Icons/Misc/skeleton.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/11/02 9:36:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=abazagaroth>Abazagaroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/11/02 10:06:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=369.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.modernhumanorigins.com/images/webring.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion about Sev: Part 2</span><hr size=1> No. The 40 person rule is what allows you to schedule, but any guild not on the RTA (or any random group of people who are not in RTA calendar/rotations guilds) can enter the planes whenever they want if no one is there yet (or maybe even if someone is there, I don't know if gms will do anything about multiple guilds in the planes). There is nothing that can be done about that.<br>
<br>
The RTA isn't the mafia, no one can come and break your legs if you don't play ball. The rotations are initially set up by the guilds that can kill the mob (if there is no rotation, and one guild that kills the mob doesn't want there to be a rotation, there isn't nothing that can be done about it other than the other guilds killing the mob to go out of their way to keep other non-rotation contested mobs unavailable to the guild, as a sort of blackmail), not by the RTA. Those guilds set up the rotation for several reasons, including prevention of fighting over it, better control over their own scheduling, and sometimes even *gasp* a willingness to share =) The RTA just keeps track of everything in one place.<br>
<br>
By joining the RTA calendar or rotation you give up your &quot;right&quot; to race for mobs/planes, for the trade of of a guaranteed shot at the mob and being able to schedule the plane. The reason the rotations are respected is because:<br>
<br>
1) They are set up by those that can kill it at the time the rotation goes into effect, so at the onset, the larger guilds are respecting the rot because they created it<br>
<br>
2) Smaller guilds respect the rotation because it is to their benefit to do so, they *will* be able to get onto the rotation if they can prove they can kill the mob. After the first kill, the &quot;race&quot; aspect is pretty much taken off the map, and smaller guilds are allowed to develop without the &quot;race race race!&quot; component smaller guilds on other servers have to deal with to progress content-wise.<br>
<br>
3) Various rotations that might not otherwise be respected due to whatever reason (like length of rotation) are respected because by breaking the rotation you are pretty much done with all rotations and must now race everyone all the time for anything.<br>
<br>
If any guild got together and said, screw rotations, we are going FCFS. There is nothing that could be done about it other than people going out of their way to not help or screw over that guild or prevent them from ever seeing some mobs. You can't petition for a gm to come punish BotS if they went FCFS and kept emp dead so that NB could never get into VT. That's just the way it is (and what happens on other servers).<br>
<br>
We all agree to be civil because the rotations allow for fair equal access. We give up the right to monopolize content so that we don't have to worry about content we want being monopolize, as well as it just making planning easier, some things less stressful, etc. The moment you take away the right of any entity to get that fair access, that entity is free to kill that content as much as they want and there isn't anything to be done about it. Regardless if they are on other rotations or not.<br>
<br>
Sure, you could put in provisions into the rotation rules to force guilds to respect such a rule, and that by racing and killing a rotation mob where another guild has already beaten/been allowed a shot at mob X, they get kicked off of other rotations. However, that just opens the door to bad feelings because you go from just administering the rotation that is self-imposed to governing the rotations as an imposed system. You are saying to entities, &quot;No, you *cannot* kill mob X, even though you aren't on the rotation and so don't have a fair equal chance at the mob as of yet, even though you can kill the mob and are there in force when the mob spawns.&quot; It partially removes the incentive for a guild to respect rotations, guaranteed access to the rotation if and when they kill the mob.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dembiredeadbones>Dembire Deadbones</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.w3.org/Icons/Misc/skeleton.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/11/02 2:29:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=369.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion about Sev: Part 2</span><hr size=1> Exactly Abaz!!  I have no disagreement with what you say for the most part, but..<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Sure, you could put in provisions into the rotation rules to force guilds to respect such a rule, and that by racing and killing a rotation mob where another guild has already beaten/been allowed a shot at mob X, they get kicked off of other rotations. However, that just opens the door to bad feelings because you go from just administering the rotation that is self-imposed to governing the rotations as an imposed system. You are saying to entities, &quot;No, you *cannot* kill mob X, even though you aren't on the rotation and so don't have a fair equal chance at the mob as of yet, even though you can kill the mob and are there in force when the mob spawns.&quot; It partially removes the incentive for a guild to respect rotations, guaranteed access to the rotation if and when they kill the mob.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The thing is we already do this as a community.  We have a Calendar for the planes, and when a person who schedules that day, the rest of the guilds let them have it out of respect to the guidelines.  Again you do not have to abide by the RTA, but for this community we all do.  But aren't we saying that Guild A has the planes reserved, so guild B cannot enter the planes?  This is not a verant rule, this is by the community, and for the sake of fair game we abide by them.  <br>
So by limiting one guild to enter the rotation at a time, is really no different than allowing only one guild in the planes at a time, cause both are saying Sorry Guild X you have to wait til next time.<br>
<br>
 <p>Dembire Deadbones<br>
60th Season Warlock<br>
Far Seekers</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nyca>Nyca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Singing Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 1298<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/11/02 2:49:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=369.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/slllyonec/EZemo/LeahHarp2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion about Sev: Part 2</span><hr size=1> The Calendar is not a rotation, it's a reservation system.<br>
<br>
You don't have to &quot;race&quot; anyone to get onto the Calendar, you only have to meet the Criteria.  You can then book a day that is unreserved.  Your reservation is then respected by the Rathe community.<br>
