 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rigorre>Rigorre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/11/02 3:41:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=369.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion about Sev: Part 2</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Your reservation is then respected by the Rathe community. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
We all know that comparing a timed spawn like Sev with a scheduled zone like Fear\Hate\PoA is like comparing watermelons and tomatoes, but why can't the rotation be considered a 'reservation' system ...or, as proposed, some kind of hybrid system where the first spawn of a turn is a race (as it is now) and the second spawn per turn is a reservation?  This is exactly what is being proposed as a compromise.  It would let one guild into the rotation each turn (via the current race policy) and would let the rotation guilds get their shot in a timely manner (via the current 24 hour reservation policy like the Planes enjoy). <br>
<br>
Yes, it is possible, perhaps even likely that there will be more than one guild wanting in the rotation at any particular turn.  Yes, this new proposal would be like telling the second non-rotation guild, &quot;no, you can't kill him&quot; ...but, truly, how is that different than the planes are now?  How, exactly, would this not work?  Guilds, even those who are not on any other rotations know of and respect the reservation system of the Planes ...why is it a leap of faith to expect them to honor a 'reservation' of Sev?  <br>
<br>
The rotation itself is a schedule ...people should be able to look at it weeks in advance and determine an approximate time where they will need to be ready to drop Sev.  That's impossible now because any number of guilds can be put on the rotation at any given turn ...throwing the whole rotation literally an unlimited and unknown number of weeks behind.  <br>
<br>
